content:
To design a custom softphone layout:

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

User permission needed: Manage Call Centers.

From Setup, enter Softphone Layouts in the Quick Find box. Click New to create a softphone layout definition or click Edit next to an existing layout definition. 

In the Name field, enter a label that uniquely identifies your softphone layout definition. Select Call Type and choose the type of call for which the currently displayed softphone layout must be used.

In the Display these call-related fields section, add, remove, or change the order of fields in the currently displayed softphone layout. Phone-related fields only appear if a valid value is available.

In the Display these Salesforce Objects section, add, remove, or change the order of links to call-related objects. Below the list of selected objects, specify which screens display when the details of an inbound call match or don't match existing records in Salesforce.

Configure softphone layouts for any remaining call types and click Save. Some features may not be available due to customizations made for your organization. See your administrator for details.
title: Designing Custom Softphone Layouts in Service Cloud
